Setup the src/fichub_net/ authentications and rl_conf files by copying the
examples (these will be mounted over in the live container):

1. cd ../src/fichub_net/
2. cp authentications.ex.py authentications.py
3. cp rl_conf.ex.py rl_conf.py
4. cd ../../dev-docker-compose

Create an authentications.py file, based on authentications.ex.py. You can
simply copy it to use the fake alexandria api included for testing:

1. cp authentications.ex.py authentications.py

To compile the ts/sass into js/css when first getting started or when making
changes to the frontend a utility image can be used via make in the project
root:
1. make frontend

Start the services:

1. docker compose up -d

This starts and initializes several components:
1. `db` (postgres), and `app-migrate` runs the sql migrations
2. `es` (elasicsearch), and `es-init` creates the initial index
3. `ax` (alexandria), fake alexandria api for testing
4. `app` -- the actual fichub.net service, flask dev mode

The container mounts the source code and runs flask in debug mode which suports
hot reloading. If changes don't appear live you may need to rebuild the
container:

1. docker compose build

Restart the app container:

1. docker compose restart app


Access the site running in the container at http://localhost:59294/ 

When using the fake alexandria, the responses it gives are based on the content
in the tests/dat/ax directory. By default you can search for and export the
"foo" fic which gets a urlId of "foo".

This currently only supports epub, the Dockerfile.dev does not currently
install calibre which is required for most other filetypes currently.

